The article is a declaration from the North American Leaders on H1N1, also known as the swine flu, issued on August 10, 2009. The leaders express their commitment to working together to address the pandemic and ensure effective strategies based on scientific evidence. They emphasize the importance of maintaining open borders for economic reasons and state that restrictive measures would not effectively prevent the spread of the virus. The leaders highlight the need for ongoing research and communication to inform public health decisions, including the use of vaccines and antivirals. They also encourage individuals to take preventive measures such as handwashing and staying home when sick. The leaders express pride in the collaboration between their countries and pledge to continue working together. They also express support for international organizations such as the World Health Organization and the Pan American Health Organization in addressing the global issue of H1N1.